eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - It has been two months since the devastating floods in KwaZulu Natal but some displaced residents are still bearing the brunt of the deadly downpour. Over 7,000 people are still homeless and have been living at community halls in the province. WATCH | KZN flood victims occupy Durban City Hall Frustrations are mounting, with residents saying promises to move them to temporary units, have not been met. Earlier this week, a group of KZN flood victims occupied the eThekwini City Hall. The residents were calling for Premier Sihle Zikalala to assist them.